		//                                  i=1
		//  i != j, and a modular representation v(x) = (v1, v2, ..., vt) of x for the m[i].
		//
		//  Output: the integer x in radix b representation.
		//
		//  1.  For i from 2 to t do the following:
		//	
		//	1.1  C[i] = 1.
